      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems representative of structural contact mechanics were solved with all three codes and results compared against analytical solutions. Errors remained within 1% for linear elastic cases, satisfying Gradation 2 numerical code verification requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies were performed for each model variant. The quantity of interest (construct stiffness at 5 mm displacement) changed by less than 2% between the medium and fine meshes, confirming discretization error is controlled at Gradation 3. Element quality metrics (Jacobian ratio, aspect ratio) were within solver-recommended bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver residuals were monitored and confirmed to converge to below 1e-6 for all load steps. Newton-Raphson convergence was achieved within 15 iterations per increment for all contact-nonlinear cases, meeting Gradation 2 requirements."
