    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The overall credibility assessment is accepted at Medium assurance level for model risk level 3. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved Gradation 2 versus required Gradation 3) is accepted on the basis of regulatory precedent for single-condition ASTM F1717 testing in 510(k) submissions and the low experimental variability observed. The FEA ensemble demonstrates mean stiffness prediction error of 4.2%, well within the pre-specified 10% acceptance threshold across N=11 specimens and two independent laboratories.",
